\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 46. A. hololeuca} Bieb. ex Besser,{\i  Nouv. Mém. Soc. Nat. Moscou}{\b  3}: 46 (1834). White-tomentose, caespitose perennial, with a stout, woody stock and numerous densely leafy non-flowering shoots. Stems (5-)20-35 cm, ascending. Leaves long-petiolate, 2-pinnatisect; lobes entire, obtuse or subacute. Capitula campanulate, in panicles. Most of the bracts entire. Involucre 3·5-4 mm, arachnoid-pubescent; bracts ovate, with a scarious margin. Receptacle glabrous. Corolla yellowish; tube glabrous and glandular. •{\i  S.C. Russia and E. Ukraine.} Rs (C, W, E).
\par

