\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 47. A. rupestris} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 847 (1753). Small shrub, with numerous procumbent, non-flowering shoots and ascending flowering stems 7-45 cm. Leaves 1- to 2-pinnatisect, sessile, glabrous or villous; lobes 2-6 × 0·5-1 mm, acute. Capitula hemispherical, nodding, in a racemose or paniculate inflorescence. Involucre 3-4 mm; outer bracts oblong, herbaceous, the inner lanceolate to ovate, with brown, scarious, long-ciliate margin. Receptacle hairy. Corolla glandular. 2n = 18.{\i  Baltic region and N.W. Russia; S. Ural and adjacent lowlands; formerly in C. Germany}. †Ge Rs (N, B, C, E) Su. ({\i Siberia and C. Asia}.)
\par

