\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 48. A. annua} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 847 (1753). Glabrous annual 5-150 cm. Lower and middle leaves 3-pinnatisect, sessile, the basal segments remote from the next pair and smaller than them; lobes 1-5 × 0·5-1 mm, linear-lanceolate, acute, entire or with few teeth; upper leaves 1- to 2-pinnatisect. Capitula hemispherical, nodding, in a lax, paniculate or (in small plants) racemose inflorescence. Involucre 1·5-2 mm, shining; outer bracts lanceolate, with a narrow scarious margin; inner ovate, with a wide scarious margin. Receptacle glabrous. Corolla glabrous. 2n = 18. S.E.{\i  Europe; widely naturalized in C. & S. Europe.} Al Bu Ju Rm Rs (C, W, K, E) Tu [Au Cz Ga Ge He Hu It Po].
