\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 49. A. dracunculus} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 849 (1753). Aromatic, much-branched glabrous perennial 60-120 cm. Basal leaves 3-fid at apex, the rest 2-10 × 0·2-1 cm, linear to lanceolate, entire or weakly toothed. Capitula globose, pedunculate, recurved. Involucre 2-3 mm; outer bracts oblong-elliptical, almost entirely herbaceous; inner ovate, with a wide, scarious margin. Corolla yellowish. 2n = 18, 36, 90.{\i  S. & E. parts of U.S.S.R.; widely cultivated for flavouring }(tarragon) {\i and locally naturalized}. Rs (C, W, E) [Au Cz Ga Ge He Ju Rm Rs (?B, K)].
