\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 50. A. glauca} Pallas ex Willd., {\i Sp. Pl.} {\b 3}: 1831 (1803). More or less densely stellate-tomentose perennial (15-)25-70 cm, with creeping or ascending stock. Leaves 1-7 × 0·1-0·7 cm, entire linear to linear-lanceolate, rarely a few (particularly on non-flowering shoots) 1- to 2-ternatisect. Capitula globose, pedunculate, patent or recurved. Involucre 1·5-2 mm, glabrous; outer bracts lanceolate; inner ovate-oblong, with a wide scarious margin. Corolla yellowish.{\i  E. Russia} ({\i Baskirskaja A.S.S.R.}). Rs (C, E). ({\i Siberia, North America}.)
