\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 52. A. salsoloides} Willd., {\i Sp. Pl.} {\b 3}: 1832 (1803). Like {\b 51} but stems usually 20-30 cm, nearly or quite glabrous; leaves glabrous or sometimes with short hairs, glaucous; middle cauline palmately 3-fid; segments 1-2 cm, subacute; capitula long-pedunculate, in a narrow, sparingly branched inflorescence; involucre 4-5 mm, glabrous; outer bracts much shorter than inner.{\i  S.C. & S.E. Russia, S. Ukraine.} Rs (C, W, E).
