\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 54. A. commutata} Besser,{\i  Bull. Soc. Nat. Moscou}{\b  8}: 70 (1835). Stems 35-60(-70) cm, herbaceous, glabrous or hairy. Lower leaves 4-8(-12) cm, 2-pinnatisect, glabrous or hairy beneath when young, long-petiolate; lobes 10-30 × 0·5-1·5 mm, linear to linear-lanceolate, acute; middle cauline leaves 1-pinnatisect sessile, the uppermost simple. Capitula oblong or broadly ovoid, pedunculate, patent or recurved, usually in a narrow panicle. Involucre 2·5-3 mm, glabrous; outer bracts broadly ovate, acute, the inner elliptical, broadly scarious. Corolla purplish or brownish.{\i  E. Russia}. Rs (C, ?E). ({\i Siberia}.)
